The paper focuses on grasping, which is a fundamental task in robotics, suggesting that it is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) category. The paper also proposes a neural network architecture for grasp detection, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a robustness classifier for training the network suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. Finally, the physical benchmarking of the proposed method suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
